   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>3.2.1882 Freitag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName> February 3. 1882</p>
            <p>
               <persName key="1118">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi> Cornish</persName> swallowed a fishbone at tea. He immediately ran out in a
               great fright. He had to read the service in chapel. I feared something appalling when
               I saw him arrive in chapel at the first sound of the bell but nothing as appalling as
               what did really happen. When he came in the first thing he did was to give out the
               hymn which was to be sung in the middle of the service before service had begun. The
               consequence was that when we came to the part where the hymn had to be sung there was
               no hymn to be sung. But this was not all; he was so &#x201e;distrait&#x201c; that he read the first
               collect for Grace but quite forgot to read the two others and directly went on to the
               prayers for all conditions of men. I laughed so much that I was every moment afraid
               that I should burst out. and make an awful noise. Of what misfortunes an inocent fish
               bone can be the cause!</p>
         </div>
